quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  27,67,"And those who disbelieved say: are we brought out when we and our fathers become dust"
  27,68,We and our fathers have certainly been promised this in the past. This is only stories of the earlier ones
  27,69,"Say: travel throughout the earth and see what the end of the guilty ones was"
  27,70,"And do not be sad about them, and do not be troubled from what they plot"
  27,71,"And they say: when is this promise if you are truthful"
  27,72,"Say: perhaps, some of that which you want to be rushed is right behind you"
  27,73,"And indeed your Master is graceful to the people, but most of them do not thank"
  27,74,And your Master indeed knows what their chests hide and what they disclose
  27,75,And there is nothing hidden in the sky and on the earth unless it is in a clear book
  27,76,Indeed this Quran tells the children of Israel most of what they disagree about it
  27,77,And indeed it is a guide and a mercy for the believers
  27,78,"Indeed your Master judges between them with His command, and He is the powerful and the knowledgeable"
  27,79,"So put your trust in God, indeed you are on the clear truth"
  27,80,"Indeed you cannot make the dead hear, or make the deaf hear the call when they turn their back going away"
  27,81,And you are not a guide to the blind from their getting lost. You can only make someone listen who believes in Our signs and they are submitted
  27,82,"And when the word (of punishment) happens to them, We bring out a creature from the earth for them, speaking to them that the people were not sure of Our signs"